You cannot throw checked exceptions(such as `Throwable` or`IOException`) from the subscriber. The `subscribe()` method takes a `Consumer` function, without any exception declarations. However, Reactor provides the [`Exceptions`][1] utility class  which can wrap any checked exception into an unchecked exception, as follows:

```java
Mono.just(&quot;test&quot;)
    .subscribe(x -&gt; {
        try {
            throw new Throwable(&quot;Error occurred:&quot;);
        } catch (Throwable e) {
            throw Exceptions.propagate(e);
        }
    }, e -&gt; log.error(&quot;Error occurred: &quot;, Exceptions.unwrap(e)));
```

The `Exception.unwrap` is used to get the original checked exception.


  [1]: https://projectreactor.io/docs/core/release/api/index.html?reactor/core/Exceptions.html

